channel.title: How do I restore null items?
channel.description:
I have lunar and moonclan items in my server. I also have many many other items. I tried the technique of changing the IDs. That didn't work. Please tell me.
Thanks, I would appreciate it. BTW, it is a 317 client. It seems to work on the SilabSoft Client, but Silabsoft goes slow and freezes a lot!

item.description:

Jingojohn:

Do you have any model downloads? As I said, it is the client not the server, because it works on Silabsoft.

I don’t have the models, you need to get them your self. I told you how to add them, I think you can handle funding the models you need. Most likely you will need to use a higher cache client to get those items, if you can’t add them.

item.title: How do I restore null items?
item.dc:creator: @doom_j doom_j
item.description:
@doom_j wrote:

If the item is null it isn’t in the client, you have to add the item models and ints to the Client, and then add the new item ids to the server in the Item Class and the item.cfg.
